# Responsive Design Patterns

This application follows responsive design best practices using Bootstrap 5's grid system and responsive utilities.

## Responsive Grid System
The application uses Bootstrap's 12-column grid system for layout:

```html
<div class="container">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-8 offset-md-2">
            <!-- Content for medium screens and up, centered -->
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12 col-md-4">
            <!-- Full width on small screens, 1/3 width on medium screens and up -->
        </div>
        <div class="col-12 col-md-8">
            <!-- Full width on small screens, 2/3 width on medium screens and up -->
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
```

## Responsive Breakpoints
- **xs**: < 576px (Extra small devices - phones)
- **sm**: ≥ 576px (Small devices - large phones/small tablets)
- **md**: ≥ 768px (Medium devices - tablets)
- **lg**: ≥ 992px (Large devices - desktops)
- **xl**: ≥ 1200px (Extra large devices - large desktops)
- **xxl**: ≥ 1400px (Extra extra large devices)

## Responsive Utilities
- **Spacing**: Responsive margin and padding classes (e.g., `my-3 my-md-5`)
- **Display**: Conditional visibility (e.g., `d-none d-md-block`)
- **Flexbox**: Responsive flexbox utilities (e.g., `flex-column flex-md-row`)

## Mobile-First Navigation
The main navigation collapses on small screens using Bootstrap's navbar component:

```html
<nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-light">
    <div class="container">
        <a class="navbar-brand" href="/">Brand</a>
        <button class="navbar-toggler" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#navbarNav">
            <span class="navbar-toggler-icon"></span>
        </button>
        <div class="collapse navbar-collapse" id="navbarNav">
            <!-- Navigation items that collapse on mobile -->
        </div>
    </div>
</nav>
```

## Responsive Images
Images use responsive classes for proper scaling:

```html
<img src="image.jpg" class="img-fluid" alt="Responsive image">
```

## Best Practices
- Always test designs across multiple viewport sizes
- Use relative units (rem, em, %) instead of fixed units (px) when appropriate
- Implement touch-friendly elements for mobile users (adequate spacing, larger touch targets)
- Optimize assets for mobile connections (compressed images, lazy loading)
